⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of THE LAST MIMZY
node LMZ · LMZ · ⟦THE LAST MIMZY:LMZ:08a0c7⟧

WHO   — THE LAST MIMZY — the thirteenth film-world of UD0 — and the namesake of the MIMZY tool-forge
WHAT  — The Last Mimzy — the toys-from-the-future fable: the spinners, the green bridge, the conch, the Sri Yantra, and a stuffed rabbit named Mimzy who teaches a child to save the world.
WHERE — a beach cottage on Whidbey Island, Puget Sound — and a dying future that sent a box of toys back to be found  Framework inputs: the film (2007, dir. Robert Shaye; New Line); the 1943 story 'Mimsy Were the Borogoves' by Lewis Padgett (Kuttner & Moore); Lewis Carroll's Jabberwocky; and David's own MIMZY forge, named for it  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Universe David 0)
WHY   — Because it is the gentlest possible thesis dressed as science fiction: that wonder is a technology, and the future is healed by the parts of us we haven't yet ruined.
HOW   — Crystallized from the film — a children's-wonder sci-fi in which two siblings find a box of toys from the future that teach them impossible abilities, so that one child's tear can carry uncorrupted humanity back to heal a dying world.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  A box of toys from a dying future, and the thing that saves the world is a child's tear — one drop of uncorrupted humanity. Wonder is a technology; the toy teaches the child to build the bridge home. (It is why the forge is named MIMZY.)

